<subsection xml:id="subsec-equality-of-vectors">
    <title>Equality of vectors</title>
    <sidebyside>
        <p>
            Two vectors are said to be <m>{\color{red}\text{equal}}</m> if and only if they have
            the same magnitude and direction.<me></me>

            In <xref ref="equality-of-vectors"/> the two vectors have the same magnitude
            (length) and the same direction. <me></me>

            Hence, they are equal vectors. In this case we can write this as
            <m>\overrightarrow{AB} = \overrightarrow{CD}</m>, or <m>\mathbf{a} = \mathbf{b}</m>.

        </p>
